The paper discusses the design and analysis of recursive algorithms for reconstructing sparse signal sequences from compressive measurements. This problem is commonly encountered in dynamic projection imaging, such as dynamic MRI and dynamic computed tomography. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI), and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories.
